activities.message:
@exit_n0de, we are reviewing this report for disclosure and will complete that process soon.

Also, please note that as per our recent program report eligibility update, we no longer plan to accept or pay new DoS reports like this that are based on triggering a 5XX error from Twitter. Issues that result in Denial of Service (DoS) to Twitter's servers at the network or application layer are now out of scope for future reports.

Thanks you for helping to keep Twitter secure.
